<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-56-1106 </DOCNO><TEXT>Near the end of 1987, 'et' magazine asked the Federal Government, theLaender governments, political parties, top managers of entreprises andassociations, and trade union representatives to answer the followingquestions: What do you think should the future energy supply of the FederalRepublic of Germany look like? Where do you think does the coal policyfit in? Do you think that the creation of a common home market of theEC as from 1992 will prove to be an opportunity or rather a burden forour energy economy? The following statements give a fairly comprehensiveoverview on the present-day positions held by decision-makers and institutionsof our society who are relevant for energy policy.</TEXT></DOC>